search:nodejs-express-mongodb-performanc.content:
- Use `npm install express mongoose` to install Express.js and Mongoose.
- Configure MongoDB connection in Express using `mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/mydatabase', { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true })`.
- Set up Nginx as a reverse proxy with the following configuration:
  ```nginx
  server {
      listen 80;
      server_name yourdomain.com;

      location /api/ {
          proxy_pass http://localhost:3000/;
          proxy_http_version 1.1;
          proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
          proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
          proxy_set_header Host $host;
          proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
      }
  }
  ```
- Use `docker-compose.yml` to define and run multi-container Docker applications:
  ```yaml
  version: '3'
  services:
    web:
      image: node:16
      volumes:
        - .:/usr/src/app
      working_dir: /usr/src/app
      command: npm start
    mongo:
      image: mongo:latest
      volumes:
        - mongo-data:/data/db
  volumes:
    mongo-data:
  ```
- Monitor Node.js memory usage with `node --inspect-brk app.js` and use Chrome DevTools for debugging.
- Implement caching strategies in Express using middleware like `express-cache-middleware`.
- Optimize MongoDB queries by indexing frequently queried fields.
